videos.description: Tom Waddle explains why he isn't shocked that the Falcons beat the previously undefeated Panthers in a division game and why Carolina shouldn't consider it a "good loss."
videos.headline: Panthers' loss surprising but not shocking

tracking.trackingName: COM_NFL Analysis (Panthers loss surprising, but not shocking) 2015/12/27 SC

videos.description: Julio Jones' 70-yard touchdown leap and run earned the Falcons wide receiver the game ball in his team's win. Meanwhile, kicker Graham Gano was the Panthers' most effective offensive weapon with two field goals to make up Carolina's second-half scoring.
videos.headline: Jones, Gano get game balls after Panthers upset

tracking.trackingName: COM_NFL Analysis (Panthers Falcons Game Ball WK 16) 2015/12/27 ODV
